The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for on-device inference on mobile phones, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the use of hardware accelerators, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and augmented reality (cs.AR) research. Finally, the paper discusses the design of mobile GPU-friendly networks, which is relevant to neural engineering (cs.NE) research.
